definitions.definition: A pearly substance made mainly of stacked layers of aragonite and organic matter which lines the interior of many shells; mother-of-pearl .

main_definition: ( obsolete ) A shellfish which contains mother-of-pearl . [16th–19th c.]
secondary_definitions: A pearly substance made mainly of stacked layers of aragonite and organic matter which lines the interior of many shells; mother-of-pearl . [from 17th c.]
